   "source": [
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "Document classification is a supervised machine learning task in which documents are assigned to predefined categories. A common application is spam filtering, where an email is classified as either **spam** or **ham** (legitimate email).\n",
    "\n",
    "For this project, I use the UCI Spambase dataset. Each row represents an email, and the predictors summarize the frequency of selected words, characters, and capital-letter patterns. The response variable indicates whether the email is spam.\n",
    "\n",
    "The goals of this analysis are to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Load and inspect the Spambase data.\n",
    "2. Explore the distribution of spam and non-spam emails.\n",
    "3. Prepare the data for machine learning.\n",
    "4. Train several classification models.\n",
    "5. Compare accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and ROC-AUC.\n",
    "6. Select and interpret the best-performing model.\n",
    "7. Examine the features that contribute most strongly to spam classification.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8944b6cf",
   "metadata": {},
