   "source": [
    "### Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "The word- and character-frequency variables generally have small values, while the capitalization variables can have much larger maximum values. This difference in scale supports using standardization for distance-based and coefficient-based models such as K-Nearest Neighbors and Logistic Regression.\n",
    "\n",
    "Tree-based models do not require feature scaling because their splits depend on ordering rather than distance.\n"
   ]
  },
