    "### Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Error analysis helps explain where the model struggles. False positives may contain words or formatting patterns commonly associated with spam even though the email is legitimate. False negatives may lack the promotional words and capitalization patterns that normally signal spam.\n",
    "\n",
    "Because the raw email bodies are unavailable, the error analysis is limited to the numerical features supplied in the dataset.\n"
   ]
