   "source": [
    "## 25. Limitations and Possible Improvements\n",
    "\n",
    "Several limitations should be considered:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. The dataset contains engineered features rather than the original email text, so methods such as TF-IDF, topic modeling, and transformer models cannot be applied directly.\n",
    "2. Some non-spam indicators may reflect the particular users and organization from which the dataset was collected, reducing generalizability.\n",
    "3. Spam language changes over time, so a model trained on historical data may require regular retraining.\n",
    "4. Default model settings were used for most classifiers. Hyperparameter tuning could improve performance.\n",
    "5. The test set comes from the same dataset as the training data. Testing on a separate modern email corpus would provide a stronger measure of real-world generalization.\n",
    "\n",
    "Future work could use raw email messages, compare TF-IDF models, tune decision thresholds to reduce false positives, and evaluate newer NLP methods.\n"
   ]
